               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Vita of Gabra Manfas Qǝddus” (fols.
                     2ra-62ra) 
 II) Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Miracles of Gabra Manfas
                     Qǝddus”: 13 miracles (fols. 62ra-78rb) 
 III) Malkǝʾa Gabra Manfas Qǝddus
                     “Image of Gabra Manfas Qǝddus” (fols. 78rb-80ra)
 
 Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1119DossierQMQ">Hagiographic Dossier of St Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="2ra" to="62ra"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1451GadlaG">Gadla Gabra Manfas Qǝddus (general record)</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="62ra" to="78rb"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3977Taammer">Taʾammǝra Gabra Manfas Qǝddus “Miracles of
                           Gabra Manfas Qǝddus”: 12 miracles</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <locus from="78rb" to="80ra"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2915RepCh196">Malkəʾa Gabra Manfas Qəddus</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#80ra">80ra</locus> ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘታቦተ፡ ማርያም፡ ማይ፡ ባአ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ወይዘሮ፡
                        ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ለጌታው፡ ብላታ፡ ባይሩ፡ ይኵኖሙ፡ መርሀ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ለገብሩ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ማርያም፡
                        ወለአመቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለደቂቆሙ፡ ገብረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወልደ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ተስፋ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡
                        ሀብተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወልደ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ተጽሕፈ፡ በ፲፻ወ፰፻{፺}ወ፪፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡
                        በዘመነ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ምኒልክ፡ ወጳጳሳቲነ፡ አቡነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ [<locus target="#80rb">80rb</locus>] አቡነ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጰጥሮስ፡ ውጉዞ፡ {ለ}ይኩን።<note> The
                           colophon states that the Ms. was donated by Walatta Mikāʾel, wife of blāttā
                           Bāyru to the church Māy Bāʾā and that the writing was finished in 1892 year of
                        mercy (= 1899/1900 A.D.) during the reign of King Mǝnilǝk II (r. 1889-1913) and
                        the tenures of Bishop Ṗeṭros (1881-1917) and Bishop Mātewos (1881-1927).</note>
                     </colophon>
