                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12918WaldaMaryamScribe">Walda Māryām</persName>
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formula, <locus target="#62ra">62ra</locus>.<date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the protagonist; name of the
                           donors; incipits of sections/miracles; word "salām" in Text III; elements
                           of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the
                           incipit page of Texts I, II and III (fols. 3r, 62r, 78r), a few lines are
                           rubricated alternating with black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
